# Cursor Rules
# These rules ensure that all generated code adheres to the project's strict architectural boundaries.

# 1. ALWAYS read the relevant AGENTS.md files before generating code.
#    - Root: /AGENTS.md
#    - Core: /core/AGENTS.md (if editing /core)
#    - Backend: /backend/AGENTS.md (if editing /backend)
#    - Extension: /extension/AGENTS.md (if editing /extension)
#    - Integrations: /integrations/AGENTS.md (if editing /integrations)

# 2. RESPECT "Forbidden Imports" logic:
#    - /core MUST NOT import 'chrome', 'react', 'express', 'backend'
#    - /api MUST NOT import 'chrome'
#    - /integrations MUST NOT import 'backend', 'api', 'chrome'
#    - /backend MUST NOT import 'chrome', 'extension', 'ui'

# 3. PREFER pure functions in /core.
# 4. USE Dependency Injection for any platform-specific side effects in /core.
